column5: Can you fish this lake? i was snowmobiling in the park yesterday and it looked like a decent lake.  If anyone has ice fished this like, if you can, whats in there?  Thanks.
Ya better know where yer going out there. As for yer ? yes you can.
never ice fished it, but fishing it in the open water season can be pretty incredible
why is that? quite a bit of current in there?

You have to be really careful on that ice. Current flows make for some skinny ice. Lost a friend up there going through the ice many years back.  As for fish there's walleye, pannies, pike, for icefishing. The days of the lakers are long gone. Last one I know of was caught in the mid 70's by one of my cousins.  On softwater, the lake has weeks worth of water to discover.  I'm a little biased. I grew up in the area, and my uncle's place was on the lake.
If you know where to go the icefishing can be great!  More of a timming thing too.
okay guys, sounds good. I'll put it on my list for one of the places to fish on the sled.  Go Home Lake McCrae Lake 12 Mile 6 Mile
